In a bowl, mix together chili powder, cumin, paprika, salt, black pepper, olive oil, and lime juice to create a marinade.

Coat the fish fillets with the marinade and let them marinate for at least 15-30 minutes.

Heat a skillet over medium-high heat. Cook the fish for 2-3 minutes per side or until cooked through and flaky.

Remove from heat and break the fish into smaller pieces.

2. Make the Cabbage Slaw:

In a bowl, combine shredded cabbage, chopped cilantro, sliced red onion, lime juice, salt, and black pepper. Toss to coat evenly.
3. Prepare the Taco Sauce:

In a small bowl, whisk together mayonnaise, Greek yogurt or sour cream, lime juice, chili powder, hot sauce, salt, and black pepper. Adjust the seasoning to taste.
4. Assemble the Tacos:

Warm the tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave.

Spread a spoonful of the taco sauce on each tortilla.

Add a portion of the cooked fish to each tortilla.

Top with cabbage slaw and sliced avocado.

Serve with additional lime wedges on the side.

5. Serve:

Arrange the assembled fish tacos on a platter and serve immediately. Enjoy the burst of flavors and textures in every bite!"
